sentences: Mark Brown (born March 8, 1962), better known by the stage name Brown Mark, also styled Brownmark and BrownMark, is an American musician, bassist and record producer.
BrownMark started working for Prince in 1981, one year out of high school.
Noted for his unique, funk-based style of musicianship, he became a record producer and recording artist himself after parting company with Prince in 1986.
Brown joined Prince's band in 1981 for the Controversy album recordings.
Brown created the funk-rock outfit Mazarati that were signed to the Paisley Park label in 1986.
After the release of the Cryptic CD entitled It's Been Awhile the group disbanded in 2002.
The CD was released late 2010 and was titled Syx mil Breach, but was immediately pulled off the market by Brown because of contract dispute with his distributors.
The Revolution was reformed in 2016 following Prince's death and went on a world healing tour to help fans mourn the loss of their mentor.
BrownMark's memoir was due from University of Minnesota Press in late 2020.

BrownMark started working for Prince in 1981, one year out of high school.
His early influences on bass are Larry Graham, Stanley Clarke, Louis Johnson, Mark Adams from SLAVE, Jaco Pastorius, Verdine White, Nate Phillips (Dazz Band) and Bootsy Collins.
He remained with Prince and was a member of The Revolution band for the Purple Rain, Around the World in a Day, and Parade albums, contributing bass and backing vocals.
These days, BrownMark is making music in his own studio; jamming, recording, and performing with inspiring musicians; and encouraging younger artists who have been influenced by his career.
